// Beat specs for `pnpm eval:pool` — the input that grows fixtures/eval/labels.jsonl.
//
// `beatDescription` mirrors the analyzer's visualDescription style (what a camera would literally
// see); `query` is the generic English stock query the search stage would emit for it (doc 07:
// real names never go in stock queries). `expect` documents intent and is NOT used by the tool:
//   servable — stock should hold a genuinely good match; tests ranking.
//   hard     — no stock asset can truly satisfy this (a named subject / specific event), so the
//              pool should come back ALL BAD. The current fixture has zero such beats, which is
//              why the abstain path — the thing §1.1's accept rule redefines — is untested and
//              precision@1 sits pinned at 100%.
